swefun.cardgames.playingcards

Class Card

  • java.lang.Object
    • swefun.cardgames.playingcards.Card

  • public class Card
extends Object
    Model cards as from a deck of playing cards. A card is represented by a Rank+Suit pair. Each unique Rank+Suit pair is also identified by a unique integer value, referred to as its ID, which may be used for new card construction.
    Version:
    1.6 $Id: Card.java 295 2017-03-24 21:26:19Z jody $
    Author:
    Dr. Jody Paul

    • Method Detail

      • generateCardID

        public static int generateCardID(Rank cardRank,
                                 Suit cardSuit)
        Utility to generate an integer card ID corresponding to the specified Rank+Suit pair.

        cardID = (cardSuit.ordinal() * Rank.values().length)) + cardRank.ordinal()

        Parameters:
        cardRank - the rank of the card
        cardSuit - the suit of the card
        Returns:
        the card ID associated with the given rank and suit
